			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	We are looking for a video engineer to help us build our next-generation multi-platform video publishing solutions.</p>
<p>
	Our job is to help our customers publish and monetize their video content on any device, anywhere in the world. You will have the opportunity to work in a diverse field of content management solutions, mobile websites, mobile apps and ConnectedTVs.</p>
<p>
	You must be prepared to work with a wide range of video and audio encoding technologies, delivery protocols and publishing tools. You also know your way around Linux, MySQL and Java. Previous experience with cloud-based solutions is a plus but not a requirement.</p>
<p>
	Your responsibilities will include creating new encoding workflows and content management practices, optimizing the flow of content from our customers to end-users and ensuring great end-user experiences for millions of people across the world.</p>
<p>
	The position offers a compensation package consisting of salary and stock options. Other benefits include a mobile phone, health care plan and paid holidays.</p>
<p>
	The ideal candidate we are looking for</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		has a start-up attitude and wants to be part of a great story</li>
	<li>
		has the flexibility required by a fast-paced, constantly evolving environment</li>
	<li>
		has experience in video technologies across different device categories</li>
</ul>
<p>
	About ThirdPresence</p>
<p>
	ThirdPresence is a cloud-based Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) platform that enables media companies and online video publishers to stream video-on-demand, podcasts and live video content to any video-capable mobile phone or tablet, including the Apple iPhone, iPad, Android, BlackBerry and Windows Phone &ndash;based devices. ThirdPresence also enables monetization of the content either by advertising, subscription or pay-per-view, and provides detailed tracking of content usage.</p>
]]></description>
